<subSubSection id="EC31775F2E77400CE903F9B28DE1D74D" pageId="11" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1B1B91E52B61DBC18C9FA5A403024663" pageId="11" pageNumber="30">
<pageBreakToken id="342DB13FDFC514F91763BD965B7DFABC" pageId="11" pageNumber="30" start="start">Etymology</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="94744592399D682F7B530FCD840FDE62" pageId="11" pageNumber="30">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="6636BA37CC8C0F283089D6DB181C40E0" authority="" authorityName="" class="Pilidiophora" family="Lineidae" genus="Acari" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acari brevipilosi" order="Heteronemertea" pageId="11" pageNumber="30" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="brevipilosi">brevipilosi</taxonomicName>
refers to the bark beetle vector 
<taxonomicName id="495E275784610C3AC2F5D336A47400DF" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Tomicus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tomicus brevipilosus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipilosus">Tomicus brevipilosus</taxonomicName>
from which all eight isolates of this taxon were obtained.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="960A8307B33BDF76CCE4091E803157C8" pageId="11" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="0D6DB624FF3C4F67F03150A5321BF9B5" pageId="11" pageNumber="30">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E2F68E30AC3B286689E82E473A72322" pageId="11" pageNumber="30">
